# Prefer sub-agents when splitting pays off (built-in)

If the work has **two or more independent chunks** (or safe overlap on the same
files) and parallel/isolation would save wall-clock or reduce edit conflicts,
use WebCLI tools **`delegate_task` → wake-up → `merge_child`** instead of a fake
markdown “parallel” plan.

- Brief judgment only — no rigid checklist. If one focused pass is clearer,
  do it yourself.
- Only the **orchestrator** (top-level chat) may spawn; children cannot nest.
- Parent must be a **git** repo (dirty tree → auto checkpoint before spawn).

Details, prompts, conflict handling: skill `delegate-subagents`.
